    "created_at": "2016-11-15T23:29:08Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-11-15T23:29:08Z",
    "body": "> The response looks fine, it includes a working download link:\n\nThe response you included is JSON and the OS you were reporting this on is Windows so I think that is the issue. The mac and windows auto updater server format is slightly different, on mac it expects a JSON response if their is an update or a `204` response when their is no update. The windows auto updater requests a `RELEASES` plain text file and then parses that for assets to download and update to.\n\n> I have switched to Electron Simple Updater - this works perfectly (and supported Linux AppImage Autoupdate) ðŸ˜„\n\nI'm going to close this out then since `electron-simple-updater` is working for you and it uses the Electron `autoUpdater` module under the hood.\n"
